---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="ProfitPath's privacy policy: what we do and do not collect. We do not require accounts, do not store Business Finder answers, and never collect your financial information."
  path="/privacy-policy"
>
  <div class="container container-narrow page-head">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Privacy Policy' }]} />
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="lead">Plain-language transparency about what we collect — and the things we deliberately do not.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="container container-narrow page-body">
    <h2>The short version</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>No accounts.</strong> You never need to register or log in to use this site.</li>
      <li><strong>We do not store your Business Finder answers.</strong> The finder runs entirely in your browser. Your answers are never sent to us or saved anywhere, and they disappear when you close the page.</li>
      <li><strong>We never collect your financial information.</strong> We do not ask for income, bank details, or payment information.</li>
      <li>We use privacy-respecting analytics to understand general site usage, and we may show advertising. Details below.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Information we do not collect</h2>
    <p>
      We do not require or request your name, email, phone number, address, or financial details to
      browse the site or use the Business Finder. The Business Finder is fully client-side: the
      questions you answer are processed in your browser to generate matches and are not transmitted
      to our servers or stored.
    </p>

    <h2>Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      We use Google Analytics for Firebase to understand aggregate, anonymous usage — such as which
      pages are visited and general engagement. This helps us improve the site. Analytics may set
      cookies or similar identifiers and collect standard technical data (such as approximate
      location, device, and browser type) as described in
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
      We do not send your Business Finder answers or any financial or personal information to analytics.
    </p>

    <h2>Advertising</h2>
    <p>
      To keep the site free, we may display advertising, including through Google AdSense. Third-party
      advertising vendors, including Google, may use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits
      to this and other websites. Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to
      serve ads to you based on your visits to our site and other sites on the internet. You can opt
      out of personalized advertising by visiting
      <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google Ads Settings</a>,
      and you can learn about your choices at
      <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">aboutads.info/choices</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      Cookies and similar technologies may be set by our analytics and (where enabled) advertising
      providers. You can control or delete cookies through your browser settings. Disabling cookies
      will not prevent you from reading the site or using the Business Finder.
    </p>

    <h2>If we ever add submissions</h2>
    <p>
      If we add features that let you submit information (for example, suggesting a business idea or
      contacting us), we will only collect what you explicitly choose to provide, we will tell you
      what it is used for, and we will require your clear consent. We will not repurpose that
      information for anything you did not agree to.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>This site is intended for adults and is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children.</p>

    <h2>Your choices and contact</h2>
    <p>
      Because we do not collect personal accounts or financial data, there is very little personal
      information for us to hold. For any privacy question, contact us via our
      <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="page-updated">Last updated: June 2026 · {SITE.domain}</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
